text: Kulpa () is a rural locality (a settlement) in Biryukovsky Selsoviet, Privolzhsky District, Astrakhan Oblast, Russia. The population was 149 as of 2010. There are 3 streets. == Geography == It is located 9 km south-east from Nachalovo. == References == Category:Rural localities in Privolzhsky District, Astrakhan Oblast
title: Kulpa, Astrakhan Oblast
